gwt.ns.transforms.client
Class CssMatrix

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
      gwt.ns.transforms.client.CssMatrix

public class CssMatrix
extends com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject

A JavaScript overlay for the CSSMatrix Javascript object. This interface is currently unsupported by any browser, but this overlay can be used for any experimental vendor implementations. The object must be created in native code, e.g. 

 final native CssMatrix createWebKitCssMatrix() /*-{
   return new WebKitCSSMatrix();
 }-* /;

See Also:
Current working draft of CSS 2D Transforms Module Level 3

rotate

public final CssMatrix rotate(double angle)
Returns a copy of this matrix rotated by angle in local coordinates. This matrix is not modified by this method.

Note: due to the implicit viewport transform (+y points down on the screen), positive angles rotate clockwise.

Parameters:
angle - The angle of rotation, in degrees
Returns:
A rotated matrix

rotate

public final CssMatrix rotate(double rotX,
                              double rotY,
                              double rotZ)
Returns a copy of this matrix which is this matrix post multiplied by each of 3 rotation matrices about the major axes, first X, then Y, then Z. All rotation values are in degrees. This matrix is not modified.

Note: the implicit viewport transform (+y points down on the screen), changes rotation directions accordingly.

Parameters:
rotX - The angle to rotate about the x axis
rotY - The angle to rotate about the y axis
rotZ - The angle to rotate about the z axis
Returns:
A rotated matrix

rotateAxisAngle

public final CssMatrix rotateAxisAngle(double x,
                                       double y,
                                       double z,
                                       double angle)
Returns a new matrix which is this matrix post multiplied by a rotation matrix with the given axis and angle. The right-hand rule is used to determine the direction of rotation. All rotation values are in degrees. This matrix is not modified.

Parameters:
x - The x-component of the axis vector
y - The y-component of the axis vector
z - The z-component of the axis vector
angle - The angle of rotation about the axis vector, in degrees
Returns:
A rotated matrix

setMatrixValue

public final void setMatrixValue(java.lang.String matString)
Replaces the existing matrix with one computed from parsing the passed string as though it had been assigned to the transform property in a CSS style rule.

Parameters:
matString - The string to parse. Can be returned by window.getComputedStyle(element).transform().
Throws:
JavaScriptException - thrown when the provided string can not be parsed into a CSSMatrix.
